---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'IMG Global in Spain', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-compliance', text: 'Spanish Visa Compliance', level: 2 },
  { id: 'spain-network', text: 'Network Coverage in Spain', level: 2 },
  { id: 'plans-and-pricing', text: 'Plans and Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'vs-local-options', text: 'vs Spanish Insurers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'claims-in-spain', text: 'Using Your Insurance in Spain', level: 2 },
  { id: 'who-its-for', text: 'Who Should Choose IMG in Spain', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Health Insurance in Spain', href: '/countries/spain/insurance' },
  { title: 'IMG Global Review', href: '/providers/img-global' },
  { title: 'IMG vs Cigna', href: '/compare/img-global-vs-cigna-global' },
];

const planColumns = [
  { key: 'plan', header: 'Plan' },
  { key: 'coverage', header: 'Coverage' },
  { key: 'spainPrice', header: 'Spain (Age 35)' },
  { key: 'visaCompliant', header: 'Visa Compliant' },
];

const planRows = [
  { plan: 'Global Medical Insurance', coverage: 'Inpatient + Outpatient', spainPrice: '$75-110/mo', visaCompliant: true },
  { plan: 'With $2,500 Deductible', coverage: 'Inpatient + Outpatient', spainPrice: '$55-80/mo', visaCompliant: true },
  { plan: 'With $5,000 Deductible', coverage: 'Inpatient + Outpatient', spainPrice: '$45-65/mo', visaCompliant: true },
  { plan: 'With $10,000 Deductible', coverage: 'Inpatient + Outpatient', spainPrice: '$35-50/mo', visaCompliant: 'Verify' },
];

const comparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'factor', header: 'Factor' },
  { key: 'img', header: 'IMG Global' },
  { key: 'spanish', header: 'Spanish Insurers' },
];

const comparisonRows = [
  { factor: 'Monthly Cost (Age 35)', img: '$75-110', spanish: '$60-120' },
  { factor: 'With High Deductible', img: '$35-65', spanish: 'Limited options' },
  { factor: 'Coverage Outside Spain', img: 'Worldwide', spanish: 'Limited/None' },
  { factor: 'Network in Spain', img: 'Smaller (reimbursement)', spanish: 'Very extensive' },
  { factor: 'Annual Maximum', img: 'Up to $8M', spanish: 'Varies' },
  { factor: 'Portability if You Move', img: 'Fully portable', spanish: 'Must cancel' },
  { factor: 'Deductible Waiver', img: '50% outside US', spanish: 'No' },
  { factor: 'Trustpilot Rating', img: '4.6/5', spanish: 'Varies' },
];

const costComparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'scenario', header: 'Scenario' },
  { key: 'img', header: 'IMG Global' },
  { key: 'premium', header: 'Premium Insurer' },
  { key: 'savings', header: 'Annual Savings' },
];

const costComparisonRows = [
  { scenario: 'Age 30, $2,500 deductible', img: '$660/year', premium: '$1,800/year', savings: '$1,140' },
  { scenario: 'Age 40, $2,500 deductible', img: '$900/year', premium: '$2,400/year', savings: '$1,500' },
  { scenario: 'Age 50, $2,500 deductible', img: '$1,320/year', premium: '$3,600/year', savings: '$2,280' },
  { scenario: 'Couple (35), $5,000 ded', img: '$1,080/year', premium: '$3,200/year', savings: '$2,120' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="IMG Global Health Insurance in Spain"
  description="Complete guide to using IMG Global in Spain. Budget-friendly international coverage with high deductible options for cost-conscious expats."
  headline="IMG Global Health Insurance in Spain"
  subheadline="The budget-friendly choice for expats in Spain. Is IMG Global's high-deductible approach right for you?"
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/countries/spain-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get an IMG Spain Quote"
  ctaButtonHref="/providers/img-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">IMG Global in Spain</h2>
  <p>
    IMG Global offers the most affordable international health insurance for expats in Spain. Their strategy: high-deductible options that dramatically reduce premiums while maintaining strong coverage limits for major medical expenses.
  </p>
  <p>
    For Spain specifically, this approach makes sense. Routine healthcare is affordable — a doctor visit costs €50-100, basic lab work €30-60. You can pay these costs out of pocket and save €100+/month on premiums, keeping your insurance for what matters: hospitalization, surgery, serious illness.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">4.6/5</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Trustpilot rating</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">$8M</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Maximum coverage</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">50%</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Deductible waived outside US</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Get a Spain-Specific Quote"
    description="See how much you could save with IMG Global in Spain."
    buttonText="Get Quote"
    buttonHref="/providers/img-global"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="visa-compliance">Spanish Visa Compliance</h2>
  <p>
    IMG Global plans are generally accepted for Spanish visa applications, though you should verify with your specific consulate. Their comprehensive plans include:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Inpatient and outpatient coverage</li>
    <li>No waiting periods for core benefits</li>
    <li>Coverage valid in Spain for visa duration</li>
    <li>Medical evacuation and repatriation</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Visa Considerations</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800">
      Some Spanish consulates prefer policies with lower or zero deductibles for the Non-Lucrative Visa. If your consulate requires this, you may need to choose a lower deductible option (which raises the premium) or consider a different provider. Always verify requirements with your specific consulate before purchasing.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h3>Documentation</h3>
  <p>
    IMG Global provides:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Certificate of coverage</li>
    <li>Policy documentation showing coverage details</li>
    <li>Letter confirming no waiting periods (upon request)</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Request Spanish translation if your consulate requires it.
  </p>

  <h2 id="spain-network">Network Coverage in Spain</h2>
  <p>
    IMG Global's direct-billing network in Spain is smaller than premium competitors. In practice, this means:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Major hospitals:</strong> Some direct billing available in Madrid and Barcelona</li>
    <li><strong>Most care:</strong> Pay upfront, then claim reimbursement</li>
    <li><strong>Any provider:</strong> You can see any licensed provider in Spain</li>
    <li><strong>Reimbursement:</strong> Typically within 5-10 business days</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>The Reimbursement Reality</h3>
  <p>
    Don't let the smaller network deter you. In Spain:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Doctor visit: €50-100 (pay, then claim)</li>
    <li>Specialist: €80-150 (pay, then claim)</li>
    <li>Hospital stay: IMG can often arrange direct billing for planned admissions</li>
    <li>Emergency: Go to any hospital; sort out payment later</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    The 4.6/5 Trustpilot rating confirms IMG pays claims reliably. The reimbursement model works fine if you have cash flow to cover upfront costs.
  </p>

  <h3>50% Deductible Waiver</h3>
  <p>
    Here's a significant benefit for Spain-based expats: IMG waives 50% of your deductible for care received outside the US. If you have a $2,500 deductible, you only need to meet $1,250 before IMG starts paying for care in Spain.
  </p>

  <h2 id="plans-and-pricing">Plans and Pricing</h2>
  <p>
    IMG's pricing in Spain is significantly lower than competitors, especially with higher deductibles:
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={planColumns} rows={planRows} />
  </div>

  <p>
    <em>Prices for worldwide coverage excluding USA.</em>
  </p>

  <h3>The Math: IMG vs Premium Insurers</h3>
  <p>
    Here's what the savings look like compared to premium international insurers:
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={costComparisonColumns} rows={costComparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <p>
    Over 5 years, these savings add up to $5,000-10,000+ depending on your age and family size.
  </p>

  <h3>Choosing Your Deductible</h3>
  <p>
    The right deductible depends on your savings and risk tolerance:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>$0-500:</strong> Maximum premium, but predictable costs. Good if you use healthcare frequently.</li>
    <li><strong>$2,500:</strong> Sweet spot for most expats. Significant savings, manageable risk. With 50% waiver, only $1,250 in Spain.</li>
    <li><strong>$5,000-10,000:</strong> Maximum savings. Only makes sense if you have savings to cover the deductible and rarely use healthcare.</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-green-900 mb-2">The Spain Strategy</h3>
    <p class="text-green-800">
      Consider a $2,500 deductible with IMG. With the 50% waiver, you pay $1,250 out of pocket in Spain before coverage kicks in. Put your premium savings ($1,000+/year) into a health savings account. After 1-2 years, you've saved enough to cover the deductible entirely — and you're still saving money every year after.
    </p>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Calculate Your Savings"
    description="See exactly how much you could save with IMG Global's high-deductible plans."
    buttonText="Get a Quote"
    buttonHref="/providers/img-global"
  />

  <h2 id="vs-local-options">vs Spanish Insurers</h2>
  <p>
    How does IMG Global compare to Spanish insurers like Sanitas or ASSSA?
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={comparisonColumns} rows={comparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Choose IMG Global If:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Minimizing premium cost is your priority</li>
    <li>You're healthy and rarely use healthcare</li>
    <li>You're comfortable with the reimbursement model</li>
    <li>You might relocate from Spain</li>
    <li>You travel frequently and want worldwide coverage</li>
    <li>You can handle a high deductible financially</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Choose a Spanish Insurer If:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>You want the largest local network with direct billing</li>
    <li>You use healthcare frequently</li>
    <li>You're staying in Spain permanently</li>
    <li>You don't travel outside Spain</li>
    <li>You prefer not to pay upfront and claim</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    <a href="/countries/spain/insurance">See all Spain insurance options →</a>
  </p>

  <h2 id="claims-in-spain">Using Your Insurance in Spain</h2>

  <h3>For Routine Care</h3>
  <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2">
    <li>See any licensed doctor or clinic in Spain</li>
    <li>Pay for the visit (€50-150 typically)</li>
    <li>Get an itemized receipt (factura)</li>
    <li>Submit via IMG's app or portal</li>
    <li>Receive reimbursement in 5-10 business days</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>For Hospital Care</h3>
  <p>
    Contact IMG before planned hospitalizations — they can often arrange direct billing with Spanish hospitals. For emergencies, go to the nearest hospital and contact IMG within 48 hours.
  </p>

  <h3>IMG Mobile App</h3>
  <p>
    IMG's app lets you:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Submit claims with photos of receipts</li>
    <li>Track claim status</li>
    <li>Access your digital ID card</li>
    <li>Find providers (limited in Spain)</li>
    <li>Contact 24/7 assistance</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Language</h3>
  <p>
    IMG's customer service is primarily English-based. Spanish documents are accepted for claims without translation.
  </p>

  <h2 id="who-its-for">Who Should Choose IMG in Spain</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Ideal For</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
        <li>Budget-conscious expats</li>
        <li>Young, healthy individuals</li>
        <li>Digital nomads watching costs</li>
        <li>Those comfortable with reimbursement</li>
        <li>Expats who might relocate</li>
        <li>People wanting catastrophic coverage</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Consider Alternatives</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>Those with pre-existing conditions</li>
        <li>People needing mental health coverage</li>
        <li>Those who use healthcare frequently</li>
        <li>Families wanting maternity coverage</li>
        <li>Expats who want direct billing</li>
        <li>Those uncomfortable with high deductibles</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <h3>How does the 50% deductible waiver work?</h3>
  <p>
    If your plan has a $2,500 annual deductible, and you receive care in Spain (outside the US), you only pay $1,250 before IMG starts covering costs. This applies to all care outside the United States.
  </p>

  <h3>Will my visa application be rejected with a high deductible plan?</h3>
  <p>
    It depends on your consulate. Some accept high-deductible plans; others prefer zero or low deductibles. Check with your specific consulate before purchasing. You may need to choose a lower deductible option for visa purposes.
  </p>

  <h3>What if I need expensive care in Spain?</h3>
  <p>
    IMG covers up to $8M per year. Once you meet your deductible, they cover 100% of eligible costs. For major expenses (surgery, hospitalization, cancer treatment), IMG's coverage is robust despite the budget pricing.
  </p>

  <h3>Does IMG cover mental health?</h3>
  <p>
    Mental health coverage is limited compared to premium insurers. If mental health care is important to you, consider Allianz Care, Cigna Global, or especially BUPA Global (which offers mental health parity).
  </p>

  <h3>Can I increase coverage later?</h3>
  <p>
    You can lower your deductible at renewal, but this may require new underwriting. If you develop health conditions while on IMG, upgrading may be difficult. Choose a coverage level you can sustain long-term.
  </p>

  <h3>Is IMG financially stable?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes. IMG has been operating since 1990 and insures hundreds of thousands of members. Their 4.6/5 Trustpilot rating demonstrates they pay claims reliably. Low premiums don't mean unreliable coverage.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Ready to Save on Coverage?"
    description="Get a personalized IMG Global quote for your situation in Spain."
    buttonText="Get Your Quote"
    buttonHref="/providers/img-global"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Pricing, coverage, and visa requirements change. We are not insurance brokers or immigration consultants. Verify all information with IMG Global and Spanish authorities before making decisions.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
